addOwner(address).details: Adds an owner to the multisig. This method can only be called by the multisig itself (i.e. it must go through the execute method and be confirmed by the owners).

params._owner: The address of the new owner.

changeThreshold(uint256).details: Changes the threshold of the multisig. This method can only be called by the multisig itself (i.e. it must go through the execute method and be confirmed by the owners).

params._owners: The initial set of owners of the multisig.

execute(address,uint256,bytes,bytes).details: Only entry point of the multisig. The method will execute any transaction provided that it receieved enough signatures from the wallet owners.

params._data: The data parameter for the transaction to execute.
params._signatures: Concatenated signatures ordered based on increasing signer's address.
params._to: The destination address for the transaction to execute.
params._value: The value parameter for the transaction to execute.

removeOwner(address).details: Removes an owner from the multisig. This method can only be called by the multisig itself (i.e. it must go through the execute method and be confirmed by the owners).

params._owner: The address of the owner to be removed.
